From c9dfbdff9548bd366d972270dfe7a0edbee82412 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ravi Minnikanti <rminnikanti@marvell.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 23:28:25 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] OSPFv3 - Fix FULL adjacency even with an MTU mismatch

ospf6d: Add automatic MTU change detection for FULL adjacencies

Implemented automatic neighbor reset when an interface MTU is modified
after the adjacency has already reached FULL state - bringing OSPFv3
behavior in line with OSPFv2.

In OSPFv2, MTU changes immediately trigger DBD exchange and cause the
adjacency to fall back to ExStart. However, OSPFv3 previously did not
react to MTU changes, allowing adjacency to remain in FULL state, which
could lead to operational inconsistencies and potential issues.

Testing:
1. Added test_ospfv3_tc5_mtu_auto_change_p0 test
2. Verified the fix on routers.

Signed-off-by: Ravi Minnikanti <rminnikanti@marvell.com>
